      % The literature suggests that attitudes become more positive towards languages as they become more endangered (Lindner 2008:18-19)
        % Among college students in Louisiana, 98% of women and 93% of men reported that Louisiana French was important to preserve (Ryon 2000:186)
        % Since, socially, there are two endangered languages here, it's not necessarily true that the same levels of positivity would occur, and as we'll see below, racial antipathy or insecurity is sometimes carried into one of these languages
        % Valdman (2007) ranked the status of langauges in Louisiana as English > Standard French > Louisiana French > Louisiana Creole (as cited in Lindner 2008:33)
